Qalaam — License Allocation
===========================

Qalaam is a multi-license codebase. Different parts of this monorepo
are licensed differently to balance moat protection (the proprietary
product surfaces) with permissive distribution of utility libraries,
adapters, and integration clients that are most useful to the
community when they remain free to fork + extend.

  apps/*                            → Qalaam Proprietary License
                                      (see LICENSE-PROPRIETARY)
  services/*                        → Qalaam Proprietary License
                                      (see LICENSE-PROPRIETARY)
  packages/*                        → Apache License 2.0
                                      (see LICENSE-APACHE-2.0)
  integrations/homeassistant/*      → Apache License 2.0
                                      (see LICENSE-APACHE-2.0)
  tooling/*                         → Apache License 2.0
                                      (see LICENSE-APACHE-2.0)
  ml/*                              → Apache License 2.0 for code;
                                      model weights distributed per
                                      upstream weight licenses

Each subdirectory's own LICENSE file is authoritative when present.
The root LICENSE-APACHE-2.0 and LICENSE-PROPRIETARY files contain
the full text of each license.

Upstream data sources (Quranic Universal Library, KFGQPC fonts,
public-domain translations, etc.) carry their own original licenses
and attributions on every record we ingest from them. See the
/credits page in the deployed app and the `*.license.json` sidecars
under `data/qul-source/raw/` for verbatim upstream license tags.

Copyright (c) 2026 Qalaam Maintainers. All rights reserved (where
not otherwise specified).

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Why mixed licensing?

The `apps/` and `services/` directories contain the proprietary
product surface — the family-tier features, the auth foundation, the
mistake heatmap, the khatm wall, the recite-and-check ASR pipeline,
the editorial-scripture UI/UX, the MCP server, the billing intake.
These represent a unique bundle that took substantial original work
to develop and is the commercial moat of the platform.

The `packages/`, `integrations/homeassistant/`, and `tooling/`
directories contain utility libraries, type definitions, the Home
Assistant integration client, and developer tooling. These are most
valuable to the community when they remain permissively licensed —
they let third-party projects integrate with Qalaam, let HACS
distribute the Home Assistant integration without licensing friction,
and let contributors send patches without IP-assignment hurdles.

The Home Assistant integration (Apache 2.0) is a thin client that
calls the Qalaam backend API. For Premium- and Pro-tier features the
backend requires a Qalaam API key issued to the user's account via
the in-app settings page. The integration itself is free; the
infrastructure it talks to is the paid product.

Anyone can read this repository; not everyone can run the proprietary
parts in production. See LICENSE-PROPRIETARY for the exact terms.
